WEBVTT

00:00:04.609 --> 00:00:08.279
The Shiramine serial femicide case.

00:00:08.363 --> 00:00:11.115
I ran away from that case.

00:00:11.199 --> 00:00:12.784
Please tell me, Professor.

00:00:12.867 --> 00:00:14.035
What really happened?

00:00:14.119 --> 00:00:17.872
I want him to be able to forget everything
and pass away in peace.

00:00:17.956 --> 00:00:19.624
Ota from the Public Prosecutor's Office.

00:00:19.707 --> 00:00:21.835
I heard you went to see Dr. Kujo?

00:00:22.418 --> 00:00:26.756
This could be a piece of a bigger puzzle.

00:01:01.249 --> 00:01:02.834
I am a forensic pathologist.

00:01:03.418 --> 00:01:06.713
My name is Masumi Mizusawa.

00:01:14.596 --> 00:01:19.809
I served as Professor Kujo's assistant
during the forensic investigation

00:01:20.768 --> 00:01:24.230
of the Shiramine serial femicide case.

00:01:29.777 --> 00:01:31.529
What's the point now?

00:01:38.828 --> 00:01:40.330
I am very sorry.

00:01:46.044 --> 00:01:47.253
Fifteen years ago,

00:01:48.713 --> 00:01:49.923
I…

00:01:51.507 --> 00:01:53.218
ran away from that case.

00:01:53.927 --> 00:01:56.888
Even though I had doubts
about the investigation results…

00:02:00.391 --> 00:02:03.436
I want to uncover the truth
behind that case.

00:02:04.479 --> 00:02:06.356
That is why

00:02:07.190 --> 00:02:08.608
I came here today.

00:02:11.986 --> 00:02:15.740
Could you please
tell me what happened back then

00:02:16.783 --> 00:02:19.118
just one more time?

00:02:28.586 --> 00:02:30.255
It has been 15 years, you know.

00:02:39.430 --> 00:02:41.891
Stop making a fool out of me.

00:02:55.613 --> 00:02:57.407
MINISTRY OF HEALTH, LABOR AND WELFARE

00:02:57.490 --> 00:03:00.284
Excuse me.
Here is this week's performance report.

00:03:00.368 --> 00:03:01.995
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

00:03:03.037 --> 00:03:04.664
Regarding MEJ,

00:03:04.747 --> 00:03:07.917
you know how the prosecution
feels about it, right?

00:03:08.001 --> 00:03:09.043
I understand.

00:03:09.127 --> 00:03:10.712
We'll look into their internal affairs.

00:03:12.422 --> 00:03:13.381
Sir…

00:03:14.424 --> 00:03:15.466
Mr. Yamazaki?

00:03:17.468 --> 00:03:19.679
Oh, good work.

00:03:26.060 --> 00:03:28.563
Having a baby is hard after all, isn't it?

00:03:29.689 --> 00:03:30.982
The nights are tough.

00:03:31.065 --> 00:03:32.734
Our little one just won't sleep.

00:03:32.817 --> 00:03:33.901
Right, I've heard.

00:03:33.985 --> 00:03:36.154
That sounds brutal.

00:03:37.280 --> 00:03:38.948
Very cute, though.

00:03:39.032 --> 00:03:42.994
They say children reward you with a
lifetime of joy before they're three.

00:03:43.077 --> 00:03:45.079
-Wow.
-I kind of understand that now.

00:03:45.163 --> 00:03:47.123
A lifetime of joy, huh?

00:03:47.790 --> 00:03:50.418
I haven't seen my parents in a while…

00:03:54.964 --> 00:03:57.133
Hello, this is Medical Examiner Japan.

00:03:59.260 --> 00:04:02.388
The deceased is 75-year-old Hideo Susaki.

00:04:02.472 --> 00:04:06.184
A ward official got worried
after Susaki didn't show up for a meeting.

00:04:06.267 --> 00:04:08.770
The landlord opened the apartment
with a master key

00:04:08.853 --> 00:04:10.521
and found him deceased.

00:04:10.605 --> 00:04:13.274
It appears that three to four days
have passed since his death.

00:04:13.358 --> 00:04:15.026
A so-called "lonely death."

00:04:15.109 --> 00:04:16.652
They happen a lot lately.

00:04:16.736 --> 00:04:20.323
The Ministry of Health, Labor and Welfare
is also taking measures,

00:04:20.406 --> 00:04:22.533
but the reality is quite difficult.

00:04:22.617 --> 00:04:26.245
We know from Susaki's past medical records
that he had chronic conditions

00:04:26.329 --> 00:04:28.748
such as heart failure
and high blood pressure.

00:04:28.831 --> 00:04:32.752
So that means it was
a natural death, maybe?

00:04:32.835 --> 00:04:36.756
Still, the possibility of murder
cannot be ruled out yet.

00:04:37.757 --> 00:04:40.510
This was left on the desk.

00:04:40.593 --> 00:04:42.428
I WON'T FORGIVE YOU

00:04:42.512 --> 00:04:46.224
There's an injury on the back of his head,
probably from hitting it hard.

00:04:46.307 --> 00:04:50.311
The police intend to continue
the investigation

00:04:50.395 --> 00:04:54.649
under the assumption that Mr. Susaki
was murdered over an altercation.

00:04:56.109 --> 00:04:58.694
The wound is a bit old.

00:04:59.987 --> 00:05:02.657
We won't know for sure
until we run an accurate test,

00:05:02.740 --> 00:05:05.660
but from the state of blood coagulation
around the wound

00:05:05.743 --> 00:05:08.037
and the progress of the swelling,

00:05:08.121 --> 00:05:12.083
it is highly likely
that this wound was formed a while ago

00:05:12.166 --> 00:05:14.544
and was left untreated.

00:05:15.169 --> 00:05:17.088
Also, the bodily fluids

00:05:17.964 --> 00:05:19.799
have left a rather large mark.

00:05:19.882 --> 00:05:21.843
Judging from the condition of the body,

00:05:21.926 --> 00:05:24.679
it appears that he was
significantly weakened.

00:05:24.762 --> 00:05:26.597
He didn't pass away immediately,

00:05:26.681 --> 00:05:29.892
but was likely unable
to move from that spot,

00:05:29.976 --> 00:05:32.854
remaining there for a long time
as he grew weaker.

00:05:34.147 --> 00:05:38.484
Even so, the body
is now lying near the entrance.

00:05:43.865 --> 00:05:45.032
What about his family?

00:05:46.534 --> 00:05:49.162
There was no relative
who could be contacted.

00:05:49.245 --> 00:05:51.330
Seems like he has no close family.

00:05:56.377 --> 00:05:58.129
Twenty-six degrees.

00:05:58.212 --> 00:05:59.046
Yes.

00:06:00.798 --> 00:06:01.924
Let's begin.

00:06:05.303 --> 00:06:08.848
The contusion on the scalp
on the back of his head

00:06:08.931 --> 00:06:12.602
seems to have occurred
about two weeks before Susaki passed away.

00:06:12.685 --> 00:06:13.603
Furthermore,

00:06:13.686 --> 00:06:18.107
there was an abrasion-like wound
all over his right arm below the elbow.

00:06:18.191 --> 00:06:20.443
This does not appear to be from a fall.

00:06:21.777 --> 00:06:24.572
A chronic subdural hematoma
was also confirmed.

00:06:24.655 --> 00:06:29.410
Bleeding occurred inside the brain
after an injury, and slowly grew worse.

00:06:30.119 --> 00:06:32.622
With a hematoma of this size,
it is highly likely

00:06:32.705 --> 00:06:35.917
that he was showing symptoms
of limb paralysis and couldn't walk.

00:06:36.459 --> 00:06:41.672
That might be why Mr. Susaki
was unable to move for a long time.

00:06:41.756 --> 00:06:45.426
However, the hematoma
is not the direct cause of death.

00:06:46.385 --> 00:06:48.763
We found dilation in the left ventricle.

00:06:48.846 --> 00:06:51.599
We are now waiting for
the tissue biopsy results.

00:06:51.682 --> 00:06:53.809
We'll add chemical testing.

00:06:53.893 --> 00:06:55.770
The cause of death is still unknown?

00:06:57.355 --> 00:07:02.360
We've observed multiple symptoms,
but none are the decisive cause of death.

00:07:02.443 --> 00:07:03.444
What about foul play?

00:07:03.527 --> 00:07:05.571
We don't know that yet either.

00:07:06.239 --> 00:07:09.242
Why did he collapse near the entrance,

00:07:09.825 --> 00:07:12.078
and how did he get the wound
on his right arm?

00:07:12.161 --> 00:07:14.455
For now, it's a mystery.

00:07:19.627 --> 00:07:21.295
YOSHIMOTO

00:07:21.379 --> 00:07:23.381
-Thank you!
-Thank you all!

00:07:23.464 --> 00:07:25.925
-That was great applause from you all.
-I know!

00:07:26.509 --> 00:07:28.386
Thank you very much!

00:07:37.478 --> 00:07:43.276
Why does it get this messy
in just one week?

00:07:46.737 --> 00:07:49.240
At least throw the garbage
into the trash can.

00:07:49.824 --> 00:07:51.367
I always tell you that, right?

00:07:53.119 --> 00:07:54.453
Got it?

00:08:00.668 --> 00:08:05.381
I'll make a batch of food again today
and leave it in the fridge.

00:08:06.048 --> 00:08:07.258
Make sure to eat it.

00:08:08.134 --> 00:08:09.844
Don't worry about it.

00:08:13.639 --> 00:08:16.851
I've told you many times
that you don't need to come anymore.

00:08:17.643 --> 00:08:19.770
If you collapse all by yourself,

00:08:21.480 --> 00:08:23.691
nobody will know, right?

00:08:25.776 --> 00:08:27.445
I don't care if that happens.

00:08:29.614 --> 00:08:31.198
That's not okay.

00:08:33.326 --> 00:08:34.410
I'm going to sleep.

00:08:55.389 --> 00:08:56.599
Good morning.

00:08:57.642 --> 00:08:58.851
Good morning.

00:09:18.287 --> 00:09:22.124
Is there something bothering you
regarding Mr. Susaki's case?

00:09:22.625 --> 00:09:23.459
Well…

00:09:24.919 --> 00:09:27.254
Somehow, I can see my father in him.

00:09:30.299 --> 00:09:32.051
A little while ago,

00:09:32.134 --> 00:09:36.514
my father retired from the workplace
where he worked for so long,

00:09:37.139 --> 00:09:38.808
and right at that time,

00:09:38.891 --> 00:09:41.519
my mother suddenly
passed away from an illness.

00:09:43.229 --> 00:09:44.522
After that,

00:09:45.189 --> 00:09:47.316
he became like an empty shell.

00:09:48.359 --> 00:09:50.111
He has been in low spirits,

00:09:50.194 --> 00:09:54.490
just spacing out all by himself
inside the house all the time.

00:09:56.909 --> 00:09:58.953
My father lives alone, too.

00:09:59.954 --> 00:10:04.333
I just can't think of Mr. Susaki's
situation as someone else's business.

00:10:10.423 --> 00:10:11.632
Yoshimoto.

00:10:13.217 --> 00:10:16.762
Could you go to
Mr. Susaki's apartment for me?

00:10:16.846 --> 00:10:17.805
What?

00:10:18.889 --> 00:10:20.516
Me?

00:10:22.518 --> 00:10:27.523
I believe you will notice things
no one else would.

00:10:33.279 --> 00:10:37.158
They say Masumi Mizusawa met with
Shinichi Serizawa from the Shiramine case.

00:10:37.241 --> 00:10:39.702
A contact came from the Ministry just now.

00:10:39.785 --> 00:10:42.913
He also visited Prof. Kujo
a while ago, right?

00:10:42.997 --> 00:10:45.291
Is it really safe
to just leave him at large?

00:10:46.375 --> 00:10:48.043
Ota.

00:10:52.840 --> 00:10:53.674
Yes, sir.

00:10:54.633 --> 00:10:57.052
Mizusawa Masumi, was it?

00:10:57.928 --> 00:11:00.973
He is a bit of an eyesore, isn't he?

00:11:02.141 --> 00:11:03.768
Please take care of it

00:11:04.602 --> 00:11:06.687
while we still can.

00:11:09.064 --> 00:11:10.274
Understood.

00:11:21.994 --> 00:11:24.455
I want to uncover the truth
behind that case.

00:11:25.039 --> 00:11:27.374
Stop making a fool out of me.

00:11:37.134 --> 00:11:38.177
SUMIRE HOUSE

00:11:38.260 --> 00:11:41.388
Do you remember
the last time you saw Mr. Susaki?

00:11:42.014 --> 00:11:43.599
I didn't see him.

00:11:44.099 --> 00:11:47.269
Mr. Susaki was always behind on his rent.

00:11:47.895 --> 00:11:50.231
I came to collect it
at the end of last month.

00:11:50.814 --> 00:11:52.816
I rang the bell, and that was it.

00:11:52.900 --> 00:11:55.027
Do you remember the exact date?

00:11:55.110 --> 00:11:57.279
It was the last Friday of the month.

00:11:57.363 --> 00:12:00.407
That's the day
I always come to collect the rent.

00:12:01.075 --> 00:12:03.452
It was around the time
of the evening chime.

00:12:03.536 --> 00:12:05.579
-Did you notice anything strange?
-No…

00:12:05.663 --> 00:12:09.416
He didn't respond,
but I heard some rustling from inside.

00:12:09.500 --> 00:12:11.502
He must have been in there.

00:12:55.421 --> 00:12:56.630
Wow.

00:12:57.214 --> 00:12:58.299
What's wrong?

00:12:58.382 --> 00:13:02.094
The inside of the refrigerator
is incredibly well-organized.

00:13:02.177 --> 00:13:04.054
The seasonings are all there,

00:13:04.138 --> 00:13:06.557
and there are plenty
of half-used vegetables too.

00:13:06.640 --> 00:13:08.058
You're right.

00:13:14.732 --> 00:13:17.818
Igawa, how tall are you?

00:13:18.444 --> 00:13:20.237
I'm 168 centimeters.

00:13:21.196 --> 00:13:22.615
Can you reach that?

00:13:46.263 --> 00:13:47.765
Listen, Yukiko.

00:13:49.099 --> 00:13:51.143
On days when something good happens,

00:13:51.226 --> 00:13:54.271
you mark it with a red circle like this.

00:13:54.772 --> 00:13:55.981
When you do that,

00:13:56.065 --> 00:13:58.942
it makes you want to fill it
with even more circles,

00:13:59.526 --> 00:14:01.111
and even an ordinary day

00:14:01.195 --> 00:14:03.447
turns into a good day.

00:14:03.530 --> 00:14:04.948
It's true.

00:14:06.283 --> 00:14:07.242
Try it.

00:14:19.797 --> 00:14:21.340
Are these…

00:14:25.052 --> 00:14:28.847
They're supermarket receipts, right?

00:14:29.431 --> 00:14:31.517
Can I take these to look into them?

00:14:32.101 --> 00:14:33.018
Go ahead.

00:14:34.019 --> 00:14:36.855
Recently, we've been getting
attention from the media,

00:14:36.939 --> 00:14:40.985
and I feel that MEJ is
becoming better known to the public.

00:14:41.068 --> 00:14:42.236
That's why right now--

00:14:42.319 --> 00:14:45.280
We have officially decided
to disband the MEJ

00:14:45.364 --> 00:14:46.740
at the end of this month.

00:14:47.366 --> 00:14:48.200
What?

00:14:48.283 --> 00:14:53.038
The higher-ups have decided it was
too early to introduce it to Japan.

00:14:54.873 --> 00:14:57.918
But it's only been a few months.

00:14:59.461 --> 00:15:03.298
Are you actually looking through
the reports we submit every week?

00:15:03.382 --> 00:15:06.010
Those were just to gather data.

00:15:08.470 --> 00:15:11.640
To decide whether to
officially introduce it or not.

00:15:12.933 --> 00:15:14.685
Besides, Dr. Mizusawa…

00:15:16.311 --> 00:15:17.813
No, never mind, actually.

00:15:19.314 --> 00:15:21.066
But aren't you glad?

00:15:21.150 --> 00:15:24.319
Now, you can finally come back.

00:15:38.292 --> 00:15:40.044
AUTOPSY REPORT

00:15:46.383 --> 00:15:48.302
AUTOPSY REPORT

00:16:05.736 --> 00:16:07.029
I'm home!

00:16:07.905 --> 00:16:10.574
The supermarket was really crowded.

00:16:11.075 --> 00:16:15.204
I found an amazing watermelon,
so I bought--

00:16:17.539 --> 00:16:18.749
Dad?

00:16:19.583 --> 00:16:20.834
Dad!

00:16:20.918 --> 00:16:21.960
Dad, are you okay?

00:16:23.128 --> 00:16:24.797
Don't be so dramatic.

00:16:24.880 --> 00:16:27.174
I just tripped.

00:16:28.008 --> 00:16:29.009
Oh, my goodness.

00:16:32.846 --> 00:16:34.723
Did you think I had dropped dead?

00:16:38.477 --> 00:16:40.187
Oh, that hurts.

00:16:46.026 --> 00:16:48.695
The contents of the refrigerator
were well-organized,

00:16:48.779 --> 00:16:51.782
and there were plenty
of half-used vegetables and seasonings.

00:16:51.865 --> 00:16:52.783
However,

00:16:52.866 --> 00:16:57.454
the cooking utensils
were stored quite high up on the shelf.

00:16:58.080 --> 00:17:02.251
Igawa, who is 168 centimeters tall,
could barely reach them by jumping.

00:17:02.334 --> 00:17:06.380
I think it would be difficult for
Mr. Susaki, who was using a cane,

00:17:06.463 --> 00:17:08.715
to get them by himself.

00:17:08.799 --> 00:17:10.717
So, in other words…

00:17:11.301 --> 00:17:15.430
Mr. Susaki wasn't alone, was he?

00:17:20.269 --> 00:17:23.814
We found receipts from shopping
at Super Sakura every Friday.

00:17:24.398 --> 00:17:27.818
There are eight receipts in total,
starting from March 13th.

00:17:27.901 --> 00:17:33.323
There was a calendar with red circles
marking the same dates as the receipts.

00:17:34.158 --> 00:17:37.411
Maybe someone was grocery shopping
for Mr. Susaki, then?

00:17:37.494 --> 00:17:40.330
But the note left at Susaki's house said,

00:17:40.414 --> 00:17:42.583
"I won't forgive you," right?

00:17:42.666 --> 00:17:44.376
Isn't it also possible

00:17:44.459 --> 00:17:47.671
that this other person
is the one who killed Susaki?

00:17:48.463 --> 00:17:51.341
And then he collapsed
on his way to the front door

00:17:51.425 --> 00:17:53.260
seeking help, or something like that.

00:17:53.886 --> 00:17:56.763
We are still missing pieces.

00:17:59.474 --> 00:18:03.854
We might find something by checking
the supermarket's security cameras.

00:18:03.937 --> 00:18:05.606
Right. Let's try it.

00:18:05.689 --> 00:18:06.815
Yes.

00:18:10.110 --> 00:18:12.029
Mr. Susaki's home is…

00:18:13.447 --> 00:18:17.242
His tissue biopsy results
have been sent over.

00:18:17.326 --> 00:18:21.455
Let's review the autopsy results
once more.

00:18:21.538 --> 00:18:22.915
-Yes.
-Let's check.

00:18:26.293 --> 00:18:28.378
SUPERMARKET SAKURA

00:18:29.338 --> 00:18:31.924
All right, let's start
with the first one then.

00:18:32.007 --> 00:18:32.841
-Okay.
-Okay.

00:18:33.717 --> 00:18:35.344
March 13th.

00:18:35.427 --> 00:18:39.097
The time on the receipt is 17:24.

00:18:39.681 --> 00:18:40.515
Okay.

00:18:40.599 --> 00:18:41.725
This one then.

00:18:42.559 --> 00:18:43.727
I'll play it.

00:18:56.240 --> 00:19:00.160
I'll compare the man in these pictures
against the police database.

00:19:00.244 --> 00:19:01.411
Please do.

00:19:01.495 --> 00:19:03.413
We'll go do some questioning.

00:19:03.497 --> 00:19:04.414
Please.

00:19:04.498 --> 00:19:08.752
As expected, there was
contraction band necrosis in the heart.

00:19:08.835 --> 00:19:10.045
Which means…

00:19:10.128 --> 00:19:13.590
It could be Takotsubo cardiomyopathy.

00:19:13.674 --> 00:19:15.092
As in, an octopus trap?

00:19:16.093 --> 00:19:19.888
It's a heart issue
where the left ventricle weakens

00:19:19.972 --> 00:19:23.058
due to severe emotional
or physical stress,

00:19:23.141 --> 00:19:26.812
causing the heart
to take the shape of an octopus trap.

00:19:26.895 --> 00:19:28.105
True.

00:19:28.188 --> 00:19:32.484
That would explain why no other findings
of ischemic heart disease were seen.

00:19:32.985 --> 00:19:35.362
It's usually transient,

00:19:35.445 --> 00:19:38.949
but in severe cases,
fatal examples have been reported.

00:19:40.242 --> 00:19:45.622
But what could have been
such a strong stressor for Mr. Susaki?

00:19:45.706 --> 00:19:49.418
Does it have something to do with him
heading toward the front door?

00:19:54.381 --> 00:19:56.216
AUTOPSY RESULTS REPORT

00:20:04.683 --> 00:20:05.934
Hello, sir.

00:20:06.018 --> 00:20:08.145
I'm Kiryu from Medical Examiner Japan.

00:20:08.228 --> 00:20:10.605
Could you please spare a moment
to speak with me?

00:20:11.940 --> 00:20:16.611
I have compiled a review
of our autopsy track record,

00:20:16.695 --> 00:20:21.450
along with effective strategies
for cooperating with the police.

00:20:21.533 --> 00:20:22.409
Excuse me.

00:20:22.492 --> 00:20:25.037
Could you please reconsider
the matter regarding MEJ?

00:20:25.620 --> 00:20:26.747
Please.

00:20:34.546 --> 00:20:37.132
AUTOPSY RESULTS REPORT

00:20:39.843 --> 00:20:42.220
Hey, Kiryu, what are you doing?

00:20:43.430 --> 00:20:44.723
I'm sorry.

00:20:46.016 --> 00:20:47.142
Mr. Yamazaki.

00:20:47.225 --> 00:20:48.977
I just can't give up.

00:20:49.061 --> 00:20:50.604
It has already been decided.

00:21:03.075 --> 00:21:03.992
Sorry.

00:21:04.076 --> 00:21:05.202
Thank you.

00:21:13.877 --> 00:21:15.629
Sir, excuse me.

00:21:15.712 --> 00:21:16.546
Yes?

00:21:16.630 --> 00:21:18.799
Do you make deliveries
to this supermarket every day?

00:21:18.882 --> 00:21:19.716
Yes.

00:21:19.800 --> 00:21:22.135
Twice a day, in the morning and evening.

00:21:23.303 --> 00:21:25.931
Do you recognize
either of these two people?

00:21:26.431 --> 00:21:28.141
Oh, this one.

00:21:29.810 --> 00:21:31.520
It was about three weeks ago.

00:21:31.603 --> 00:21:34.106
I happened to see him
right when I was unloading goods.

00:21:36.525 --> 00:21:40.487
The security camera at the supermarket
entrance shows him losing his balance,

00:21:40.570 --> 00:21:43.532
and hitting his head on the ground.

00:21:43.615 --> 00:21:48.203
So, that means there's no foul play
regarding the injury to his head.

00:21:49.538 --> 00:21:51.748
Which means Mr. Susaki

00:21:51.832 --> 00:21:54.960
passed away from cardiomyopathy
caused by strong stress.

00:21:55.043 --> 00:21:58.505
What about the test of the substance
found in the wound on his arm?

00:21:59.297 --> 00:22:00.340
Here it is.

00:22:04.094 --> 00:22:06.054
Plant fiber…

00:22:06.138 --> 00:22:07.722
From the tatami flooring.

00:22:07.806 --> 00:22:11.768
It would require a fairly strong force
to result in this kind of injury.

00:22:12.394 --> 00:22:15.772
Unable to move due to paralysis
and being weakened,

00:22:15.856 --> 00:22:19.860
Mr. Susaki desperately tried to head
toward the front door,

00:22:19.943 --> 00:22:24.406
dragging his entire body weight
with his right arm.

00:22:34.207 --> 00:22:35.041
Yes?

00:22:37.711 --> 00:22:38.795
I'll be right back.

00:22:40.172 --> 00:22:41.631
They found the man from the receipt.

00:22:41.715 --> 00:22:42.591
What?

00:22:42.674 --> 00:22:44.759
He was being held in custody for theft.

00:22:59.900 --> 00:23:00.734
Go ahead.

00:23:07.324 --> 00:23:08.491
Now then.

00:23:08.575 --> 00:23:11.828
Please cooperate with us
to help determine the cause of death.

00:23:21.379 --> 00:23:25.383
You are Yasuhiko Hayashida, correct?

00:23:28.094 --> 00:23:29.012
Who are you?

00:23:30.430 --> 00:23:35.560
My name is Masumi Mizusawa
from Medical Examiner Japan.

00:23:37.646 --> 00:23:38.939
Excuse me…

00:23:40.941 --> 00:23:43.944
but did you know Hideo Susaki?

00:23:48.865 --> 00:23:51.868
Did something happen to Mr. Susaki?

00:23:55.413 --> 00:23:56.665
He passed away.

00:24:02.420 --> 00:24:06.841
Could you tell me
what kind of relationship you had

00:24:07.801 --> 00:24:09.886
with Mr. Susaki?

00:24:16.518 --> 00:24:17.560
I…

00:24:19.688 --> 00:24:22.065
used to get in trouble a lot
when I was young.

00:24:24.693 --> 00:24:26.820
I was in prison for a while.

00:24:30.365 --> 00:24:33.952
I wanted to do honest work once I got out,

00:24:35.954 --> 00:24:38.873
but no company wanted to hire
someone like me.

00:24:40.792 --> 00:24:43.169
So I only had cheap day-labor gigs.

00:24:43.920 --> 00:24:44.879
And…

00:24:46.589 --> 00:24:48.675
when I ran out of money,
I would do it again,

00:24:50.218 --> 00:24:52.137
get caught, and repeat the cycle.

00:24:54.806 --> 00:24:56.016
Pretty pathetic, right?

00:24:58.727 --> 00:25:00.770
I wasn't even there when my parents died.

00:25:02.647 --> 00:25:04.357
Because I was in prison.

00:25:11.865 --> 00:25:14.075
SALARY

00:25:29.257 --> 00:25:30.925
About three months ago,

00:25:31.968 --> 00:25:34.679
I snuck into Mr. Susaki's apartment.

00:26:46.501 --> 00:26:47.961
You need money, don't you?

00:27:05.228 --> 00:27:06.521
What the hell?

00:27:10.358 --> 00:27:13.445
Can you… cook?

00:27:14.988 --> 00:27:16.030
What?

00:27:17.532 --> 00:27:19.367
With that 30,000 yen,

00:27:19.951 --> 00:27:21.870
make me some food, would you?

00:27:24.789 --> 00:27:27.125
You can keep all the change.

00:27:30.920 --> 00:27:32.255
I don't really know why,

00:27:33.548 --> 00:27:36.509
but he just reminded me of my father.

00:27:37.969 --> 00:27:40.305
I should have just
taken the money and ran.

00:27:44.684 --> 00:27:47.061
Before I knew it,
I was going shopping for him.

00:27:48.396 --> 00:27:54.360
CARROTS FROM CHIBA, 98 YEN
CARROTS FROM TOKUSHIMA, 118 YEN

00:28:01.618 --> 00:28:03.495
APARTMENT 101 - SUSAKI

00:28:09.876 --> 00:28:11.044
Curry, huh?

00:28:13.046 --> 00:28:14.547
Is that a problem?

00:28:15.924 --> 00:28:17.342
You eat some too.

00:28:22.138 --> 00:28:23.223
Let's eat.

00:28:57.757 --> 00:28:58.633
What?

00:29:02.011 --> 00:29:03.221
You didn't run away.

00:29:11.104 --> 00:29:11.938
Hey.

00:29:13.565 --> 00:29:15.191
Can you cook next week, too?

00:29:15.817 --> 00:29:16.943
What?

00:29:17.026 --> 00:29:18.486
I'll give you 30,000 yen.

00:29:25.451 --> 00:29:27.036
Every Friday…

00:29:27.120 --> 00:29:28.788
-Thank you very much.
-Thank you.

00:29:29.372 --> 00:29:32.709
…cooking for Mr. Susaki became the norm.

00:29:33.877 --> 00:29:34.794
I actually

00:29:36.212 --> 00:29:38.172
really started looking forward to it.

00:30:01.112 --> 00:30:02.947
I heard you on the first ring.

00:30:06.200 --> 00:30:07.619
Coming, coming.

00:30:14.751 --> 00:30:15.585
Hey.

00:30:18.212 --> 00:30:19.047
Hello.

00:30:21.633 --> 00:30:23.426
I would have preferred omurice.

00:30:26.930 --> 00:30:27.931
I didn't get eggs.

00:30:37.857 --> 00:30:39.150
I'll put it in the fridge.

00:30:39.776 --> 00:30:40.610
Thanks.

00:31:10.473 --> 00:31:12.767
The thing I made the other day
was good, right?

00:31:12.850 --> 00:31:14.227
Not particularly.

00:31:28.658 --> 00:31:30.159
Buy a phone at least.

00:31:32.370 --> 00:31:33.913
I have no one to talk to.

00:31:35.707 --> 00:31:36.708
Any family?

00:31:36.791 --> 00:31:37.792
No.

00:31:38.543 --> 00:31:39.502
Same here.

00:31:42.630 --> 00:31:45.091
Bet you don't want to be similar
to a criminal.

00:31:47.093 --> 00:31:49.887
The food you make is delicious.

00:31:54.434 --> 00:31:56.978
You can still start over.

00:32:01.649 --> 00:32:02.692
So,

00:32:03.693 --> 00:32:05.445
never commit a crime again.

00:32:12.618 --> 00:32:13.453
Okay.

00:32:30.511 --> 00:32:32.138
But I couldn't do it.

00:32:32.221 --> 00:32:34.057
No matter how much I worked,

00:32:34.557 --> 00:32:36.309
or how much money Mr. Susaki gave me,

00:32:37.101 --> 00:32:39.062
I ran out of money again.

00:32:40.313 --> 00:32:41.481
And I…

00:33:05.213 --> 00:33:06.506
Mr. Susaki said…

00:33:09.717 --> 00:33:11.719
that if I ever did it again…

00:33:14.263 --> 00:33:17.058
he would never forgive me.

00:33:21.187 --> 00:33:22.271
That's why…

00:33:23.815 --> 00:33:25.858
I couldn't bring myself to face him.

00:33:29.237 --> 00:33:30.613
There were red circles…

00:33:32.657 --> 00:33:34.659
on his calendar.

00:33:36.327 --> 00:33:37.495
Red circles?

00:33:39.205 --> 00:33:42.208
If they were for the days
you were scheduled to come,

00:33:42.917 --> 00:33:47.255
then there should have been a circle
on the coming Friday as well.

00:33:49.841 --> 00:33:50.842
But…

00:33:52.009 --> 00:33:54.053
Mr. Susaki drew them

00:33:55.429 --> 00:33:59.433
after you had already visited him.

00:34:01.519 --> 00:34:03.187
I think for Mr. Susaki…

00:34:04.897 --> 00:34:06.649
the days you visited

00:34:07.608 --> 00:34:09.443
were good days.

00:34:51.485 --> 00:34:52.320
Hey.

00:34:52.987 --> 00:34:54.947
Watch where you're going, gramps.

00:34:55.031 --> 00:34:56.073
Watch it.

00:34:57.158 --> 00:34:58.242
Got it?

00:34:58.326 --> 00:35:00.203
Come on, that's enough.

00:35:17.553 --> 00:35:19.889
On the Friday you didn't come,

00:35:20.890 --> 00:35:24.018
Mr. Susaki went to the supermarket
by himself.

00:35:25.353 --> 00:35:26.354
What?

00:35:27.563 --> 00:35:30.650
I think he might have gone
to look for you.

00:35:33.778 --> 00:35:35.404
And we suspect

00:35:36.239 --> 00:35:38.866
that when he hit his head that time,

00:35:38.950 --> 00:35:42.536
it caused a subdural hematoma to form.

00:35:44.538 --> 00:35:49.627
Mr. Susaki's symptoms also progressed
without him realizing it,

00:35:49.710 --> 00:35:51.796
gradually losing his physical freedom,

00:35:51.879 --> 00:35:53.130
and in the end,

00:35:53.214 --> 00:35:56.717
he became unable to move
even a single step.

00:35:59.345 --> 00:36:01.055
Wait a second.

00:36:04.600 --> 00:36:05.726
That means…

00:36:08.729 --> 00:36:09.981
it's my fault…

00:36:13.693 --> 00:36:14.986
that Mr. Susaki…

00:36:26.330 --> 00:36:27.790
Every Friday…

00:36:31.294 --> 00:36:33.796
right when the evening chime rang…

00:36:37.133 --> 00:36:39.885
I would open the front door
of Mr. Susaki's house.

00:36:45.933 --> 00:36:48.352
Even now, when I hear that sound,

00:36:49.729 --> 00:36:51.230
I remember Mr. Susaki's face.

00:36:57.611 --> 00:36:58.654
Mr. Susaki…

00:37:00.573 --> 00:37:01.490
I'm…

00:37:05.161 --> 00:37:06.203
sorry.

00:37:14.462 --> 00:37:16.672
I believe the cause of Mr. Susaki's death

00:37:16.756 --> 00:37:20.760
was indeed Takotsubo cardiomyopathy.

00:37:24.180 --> 00:37:27.850
It is a disease that often develops
when triggered

00:37:27.933 --> 00:37:29.977
by intense emotional stress.

00:37:32.438 --> 00:37:37.109
The intense stress for Mr. Susaki
might have been

00:37:38.402 --> 00:37:43.866
the fact that he would no longer
be able to meet you.

00:38:17.358 --> 00:38:19.193
Damn it!

00:38:22.488 --> 00:38:23.489
Damn.

00:38:23.572 --> 00:38:24.573
I WON'T FORGIVE YOU

00:39:44.904 --> 00:39:46.655
So annoying.

00:39:47.364 --> 00:39:49.241
I heard you on the first ring.

00:39:54.914 --> 00:39:56.123
Mr. Susaki?

00:39:57.041 --> 00:39:59.084
Pay the rent already!

00:40:32.076 --> 00:40:33.494
I'm the worst.

00:40:36.872 --> 00:40:37.873
Why…

00:40:40.918 --> 00:40:42.419
Why would he want me to…

00:40:44.088 --> 00:40:45.381
I think Mr. Susaki

00:40:46.757 --> 00:40:48.050
wanted you

00:40:48.842 --> 00:40:51.303
to come see him again, Mr. Hayashida.

00:42:06.962 --> 00:42:08.714
The days I came here…

00:42:11.425 --> 00:42:13.344
On days when something good happens,

00:42:13.427 --> 00:42:16.805
you mark it with a red circle like this.

00:42:25.439 --> 00:42:27.691
You don't need to come anymore.

00:42:31.820 --> 00:42:32.738
Hey.

00:42:33.238 --> 00:42:34.615
Are you listening?

00:42:35.616 --> 00:42:37.451
Stop coming.

00:42:44.291 --> 00:42:45.584
Dad.

00:42:48.754 --> 00:42:50.130
I'll come by again.

00:43:17.074 --> 00:43:18.909
What are you smiling about?

00:43:21.745 --> 00:43:25.082
I've taught my dad
how to use a messaging app.

00:43:25.582 --> 00:43:26.625
GOOD MORNING (SMILE)
TAKECA, TAKE CAR

00:43:26.709 --> 00:43:27.793
He types a lot!

00:43:28.877 --> 00:43:30.254
Your dad is cute.

00:43:30.337 --> 00:43:31.296
Is he?

00:43:31.380 --> 00:43:32.506
May I show them?

00:43:33.132 --> 00:43:34.258
Look at this.

00:43:35.217 --> 00:43:37.469
-Your dad?
-He spelled it all wrong.

00:43:37.553 --> 00:43:39.471
He tried to send it a few times.

00:43:40.848 --> 00:43:42.141
That's cute.

00:43:42.891 --> 00:43:44.601
He can't type it right.

00:43:48.230 --> 00:43:49.356
Excuse me.

00:43:50.858 --> 00:43:53.694
I have something to tell you all.

00:44:00.284 --> 00:44:01.785
MEJ…

00:44:07.750 --> 00:44:11.962
MEJ will be shut down
by the end of this month.

00:44:23.557 --> 00:44:25.976
Subtitle translation by: Maslin F.